Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely chop @chili pepper{1}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over high heat. Add @ground pork{10%oz} and @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4 servings). Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer; cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on bottom, ~{2%minutes}.

Break up pork into pieces; add @bok choy and napa cabbage{4%oz}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and half the chili (whole chili for 4). (TIP: Use less chili if you prefer a milder soup!) Cook until pork is cooked through and veggies are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

> TIP: Use less chili if you prefer a milder soup!

Stir @pork ramen stock concentrate{1}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @veggie pho stock concentrate{1}, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, 1 1/2 cups water (3 cups for 4 servings), and @sugar{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4) into pot with pork and veggies. Cover, bring to a boil, and cook until veggies are tender, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add 3/4 of the @ramen noodles{6%oz} (use the rest as you like) to medium pot with boiling water; cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Drain, then rinse noodles under cold water, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir @coconut milk{5.07%oz}, drained noodles, and a big squeeze of lemon juice into pot with soup; season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

Divide soup between bowls. Squeeze juice from remaining lemon wedges over top and serve.